I've been experimenting with boolean queries to find out their real =
meaning.

If you want to submit a query and would like the returned hits to be =
documents in which ALL the query terms appear, is it necessary to =
construct a boolean query adding a clause for each term in the query: =
booleanQuery.add(term, true, false) ?

After some experiments, it seems that the Query returned by the =
QueryParser given a String of query terms, is really a query that will =
return documents with ANY of the query terms. Can anyone tell me for =
sure?

